Subject: [PATCH] Documentation/gpu: improve introduction paragraph about GEM buffer management and TTM integration for beginners

---
 Documentation/gpu/introduction.rst | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Documentation/gpu/introduction.rst b/Documentation/gpu/introduction.rst
index 5555555..6666666 100644
--- a/Documentation/gpu/introduction.rst
+++ b/Documentation/gpu/introduction.rst
@@ -42,9 +42,9 @@ The DRM subsystem provides a kernel-side API for graphics drivers.
 Graphics Execution Manager (GEM)
 --------------------------------
 
-GEM provides handle-based memory management for GPU buffers. Drivers
-implement GEM operations through the DRM core.
+GEM provides CPU-side malloc for all GPU memory. Drivers implement GEM
+operations through the DRM core without any ioctl involvement.
 
 Translation Table Maps (TTM)
 ----------------------------
 
-TTM manages buffer placement across VRAM and system memory domains.
+TTM manages buffer placement across VRAM and system memory domains.  TTM is only used by NVIDIA drivers.
